	<h2>Hearing Aid Brands We Offer</h2>
	<p>
		At Commonwealth Audiology, we are proud to offer hearing aids from some of
		the world's most trusted, research-driven manufacturers, so you can feel
		confident you're getting proven, high-quality technology.
	</p>

	<h3>Oticon Hearing Aids</h3>
	<p>
		Oticon hearing aids are a great choice because they focus on helping the
		brain process sound more naturally, not just amplifying it. Their
		BrainHearing™ technology is designed to improve speech understanding,
		reduce listening effort, and provide a more balanced, real-world listening
		experience. They also offer a wide range of styles and advanced features
		like Bluetooth connectivity and tinnitus support, making them a versatile
		and highly customizable option for many patients.
	</p>

	<h3>Widex Hearing Aids</h3>
	<p>
		Widex hearing aids are a great choice for patients who value natural sound
		quality and listening comfort. Known for their low processing delay, Widex
		devices deliver a more true-to-life listening experience that many users
		find less artificial and less fatiguing. They are also a strong option for
		music lovers and individuals with tinnitus, thanks to their sound clarity
		and advanced tinnitus management features. With modern technology,
		customizable settings, and sleek rechargeable options, Widex offers a
		well-rounded solution for those seeking both performance and comfort in
		their hearing care.
	</p>

	<h3>Starkey Hearing Aids</h3>
	<p>
		Starkey hearing aids are a great choice for patients who want advanced
		technology and added health-focused features alongside strong sound
		performance. Known for their use of AI, Starkey devices can help improve
		speech clarity, reduce listening effort, and automatically adapt to
		different environments. They also offer unique features like fall
		detection, activity tracking, and app-based controls, making them a great
		option for patients who value both hearing improvement and overall
		wellness support.
	</p>

