		<li>Headsets</li>
		<li>Swim plugs</li>
	</ul>
	<p><strong>Benefits include:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>All-day comfort</li>
		<li>Reduced feedback and whistling</li>
		<li>A secure, reliable fit</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Assistive Listening Devices (ALDs)</h2>
	<p>
		Sometimes hearing aids need extra support in more challenging listening
		environments. Assistive Listening Devices (ALDs) are designed to work
		alongside your hearing aids, or on their own, to improve speech clarity and
		reduce background noise in situations where hearing can be more difficult.
	</p>
	<p>
		ALDs can be especially helpful in places like classrooms, meeting rooms,
		places of worship, theaters, and even at home while watching TV or talking
		on the phone. These devices bring sound directly to your ears, making it
		easier to stay engaged and connected without straining to hear.
	</p>
	<p>
		There are several types of ALDs available, including remote microphones, TV
		streamers, and amplified phone systems, each designed to address specific
		listening needs. Our audiologist will take the time to understand your
		daily environments and challenges, helping you choose the right solution
		that fits seamlessly into your lifestyle and enhances your overall hearing
		experience.
	</p>

	<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
	<Accordion>
		<AccordionItem title="Which hearing aids are the most advanced?">
			<p>
				It depends on your listening needs and lifestyle. Many of today's
				most advanced hearing aids, especially from brands like Oticon,
				Widex, and Starkey, offer features such as AI-based sound
				processing, Bluetooth streaming, rechargeable batteries, and
				sophisticated noise reduction. These technologies are designed to
				automatically adapt to your environment, improve speech clarity,
				and make listening feel more natural throughout the day.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
		<AccordionItem title="Which brands help with tinnitus?">
			<p>
				Oticon, Widex, and Starkey all offer built-in tinnitus management
				tools that can provide relief and improve overall comfort. These
				features may include customizable sound therapy, masking options,
				and integration with hearing aid amplification to reduce the
				perception of tinnitus and make it less noticeable over time.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
		<AccordionItem title="What hearing aids work best for severe hearing loss?">
			<p>
				For individuals with severe to profound hearing loss, high-powered
				hearing aids from manufacturers like Oticon and Starkey can provide
				excellent support. These devices are designed to deliver greater
				amplification while maintaining sound clarity, and often include
				advanced feedback management and speech enhancement to improve
				communication in a variety of environments.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
		<AccordionItem title="How long do custom ear molds last?">
			<p>
				Most custom ear molds last between 2–5 years with proper care.
				Their lifespan can vary depending on factors like wear and tear,
				changes in ear shape, and how well they are maintained. Regular
				check-ups can help ensure they continue to fit properly and perform
				as intended.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
		<AccordionItem title="Is it safe to sleep with custom earplugs?">
			<p>
				Yes, custom earplugs designed specifically for sleep are safe when
				used as directed. They are made to fit comfortably in the ear
				without causing pressure, and when kept clean, they provide an
				effective and comfortable way to reduce noise and support better
				rest.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
	</Accordion>

